reviews.text:
Hands down wonderful experience. I got there and wandered through the back area for a bit and looked at some of the area where they grow grapes, and then walked into the area where they do tastings. Because the weather was so gorgeous, they offered us seats outside which was so lovely! The seating area is covered, which is nice because the sun was a bit bright, and the tables and decor are so cute!

Onto the tasting - GOOD DEAL. $10 for 5 wines, plus they did a complimentary one at the end! And you get to keep your glass! What a deal. And the pours? GENEROUS. Definite tip: if you're planning on driving afterwards, plan to spend at least an hour here or eat something while drinking.

Speaking of eating, they offer a cheese plate ($5 per person) and it's pretty tasty!

I'd go back here in a heartbeat, especially if the weather is nice.
Great experience wonderful owners that made my wife and I feel at home

Amazing winery! $10 to taste 5 wines and you get to keep the glass. We went for a bachelorette party and it was perfect. The bride’s tasting was also free. The owner and his son are both so nice and their set-up is super cute. The wines are also very tasty, I recommend buying a bottle of the cranberry for home. I would give them more stars if I could. Thanks for the amazing experience!

The tasting was $10 for a flight of 5 wines plus one bonus taste. After three pours they came in and asked for our last taste what we would like. After a bit of a discussion they came up with the last three tastes but we ended up with the same wines again. The wine wasn’t bad but their knowledge of wine and sequencing for tasting leaves a lot to be desired. Save your time.  Not worth the stop. They lack a lot in terms of a winery experience. The ladies doing the pouring were more like bartenders than knowledgeable wine folks.
Love this place! Great atmosphere and great wine! #shoplocal

Great location for weddings. We had our wedding here and it was absolutely perfect. Recommend doing the stations set up for food for the variety, abundance, and affordability (did mention it comes with an all you can eat raw bar?!). If you book a Saturday day wedding, it is much cheaper because they usually charge extra for the room if you book their Saturday evening wedding slot. Very spacious. Good sized dance floor. They also have several wedding coordinators to make sure your day is perfect and on your wedding day, you have your own personal server who makes sure you get whatever food or drink you want so you don't even miss out on cocktail hour appetizers! As a wedding revenue, would give this place 5 stars. Have also eaten at the restaurant and would give the restaurant 4 stars mostly due to the service being a bit slow. Excellent clam chowder.

This place was outstanding! The food was excellent rooms comfortable and clean. They even accommodated our chocolate lab puppy!  The staff was friendly and accommodating. Even gave us a discount on our return or to use at any of their other great hotels. Thank you for making our winter getaway wonderful! Great location right near the ferry to MV. I

Really nice Sunday brunch. Lots of selection, both breakfast and Sunday dinner type food, and a considerable dessert selection. Service was prompt, friendly, we were encouraged to have a long, leisurely meal. Plus the coffee was delicious. Just go there. We'll certainly return again soon.
Sunday brunch is still good, but the dinners and service just isn't as good.

The front desk staff and the rooms were great. We just did a 1 bedroom room and it was spacious, had a fridge and had everything you would need. The continental breakfast was normal and didn't have anything exciting. The restaurant mad good drinks but we didn't stay for dinner.

Love the new calendar dates for live music!! What a beautiful location. Drinks are expensive, but if a nondrinker.plenty of water available..as long as the bartender doesn't keep dumping them.Older crowd, average age 60ish,but depends on the band,love Walrus Gumboot and PUSH!

Had my junior prom here year ago and went to a friend's wedding here recently. Great location for such events as it is right on the water and also very affordable. They, as well as their sister restaurant, the Coonamessett Inn, both offer a stations set up meal for weddings, which I highly recommend for it's affordability and wide variety (not to mention all you can eat raw bar). It allows guests to eat as soon as they arrive and mingle rather than forcing them to wait an hour or two for a sit down meal with limited options.

If you’re looking for an amazing ambience and outdoor dining for super fresh seafood in late spring, summer or fall, don’t skip the Flying Bridge restaurant sitting right on Falmouth Harbor. They also seat inside during chilly months. The menu is expansive with a dozen species of seafood from North and South America. Deep fried, baked or grilled, you can experience a host of tasty dishes, each with its own twist and variation. The onion rings which come the size of a small mountain are the best I’ve ever had, hands down. Service is always friendly and food is mouth watering good. You won’t be disappointed!
Our first night in Falmouth and we were recommended to eat at the Flying Bridge.  Great dinner and wonderful host and servers....we'll be back before heading back to KY!
Right on the harbor the view is very nice and the staff friendly. Food was good. I had a lobster salad and Bill had fish and chips. It was very relaxing.

Nice resort with pools heated and right next to the beach. Loved the kitchen. Some things need updating but overall clean and pleasant. Only down side was guest leaving towels around the pools and they are not picked up readily by staff.

This place is awesome. They're right on the beach and the view is amazing.  They have a very friendly and helpful staff and the prices are very reasonable compared to other places.  I didn't find any bed bugs or any other issues that a lot of other places have reports about... I would highly recommend staying here when coming to this city

The place looks alot nicer from the outside than inside. The price was higher than what it was actual worth. Front desk staff weren't very helpful and some even had attitudes. You only get one parking pass per room and parking is limited (there Is public parking next street over to the right face the ocean but it is very limited). The rooms were decent but should be improved. Small bathrooms. VERY uncomfortable bed sheets which is off putting. House keeping DID NOT clean the room daily, only brought new towels. They have a water park for kids but the water do not look clean at all. 
Wouldn't come back unless I had to.
We have stayed here several times and love it. Always clean, staff is nice, and the accommodations are great. Can't beat the views for the oceanfront suites! We will be back!
I actually stay here every year...my kids love it. Nice and clean and very kid friendly. Literally they never want to leave the hotel when we come!

Molly's took a last minute reservation for a birthday celebration for seven of us. We could not have been happier. The food, the tea and the service were all terrific. This made my family members very happy.
Great selection of teas (hot and cold). Friendly staff and a quiet lunch atmosphere. Had a roast beef sandwich that was fantastic.

Beth made our experience AMAZING. We were served with such warm, genuine grace. The food was so good. I had the crabmeat sandwich, my mom had a grilled caprese sandwich special. It has a great atmosphere, good music, and excellent service.
A lovely little tea room with delectable scones and various other goodies. Paula was our waittress and took such good care of us. The kind of place you want to return to again and again.

Lovely place to get a light lunch. My husband and I shared a Queen's Tea, which included a scone, we purchased a second one, small pastry cups, small croissants,and various breads filled with chicken, crab, curried chicken, tuna & egg salads or sliced cucumber with cream cheese. Although the pastry seemed purchased, the filling was apparently made on the premises. There were 4 small sweets,just enough to top off a meal. We each had a cup of clam chowder which was also good. It was enough for the two of us &we took the sweets with us to nibble on later. I only wish the tea pot had been large enough for us each to have 2 full cups.

We didn't actually eat there, we were hurrying to get there before 7:45 pm which Google has listed as the close time, but, be advised, they stop taking orders at 7:30, which we just missed. But, the place looks great, spectacular location, the food smelled wonderful and all the patrons looked very happy. Hope to go there next summer for sure!

Harbor view, check. Weathered shack, check. Outdoor seating to watch the boats go by, check. Delicious clams and seafood, check. The perfect cliche of what a clam shack should be. Just make sure to bring cash! I don't believe they take cards.
Always tasty...very casual...cash only. Limited indoor seating, picnic tables on the dock and some on the roof.  Nice view of the marina.
The name is pretty accurate. Lots of seating, quick no nonsense serving and delicious fried seafood. I would recommend the fried oyster bellies on a roll with a coke.

My family has been coming to the Clam Shack for so many years and it never disappoints! Super yummy food and the best fried clams on Cape Cod by far! You cannot beat the view either! Thank you Clam Shack!

This place is a tiny shop that has slowly expanded to a small shop and I love it. We had the chocolate mousse pie today which was perfect! I also tried their coffee special, a raspberry mocha, it was oh my god delicious. I would definitely recommend visiting this spot, I'll be bringing the rest of my family later in the week!

Love this place.  Small Town bakery/cafe.  Huge pastries all tasting great.  Outside eating great location in woodshole.  Great service /, not just a seasonal stop.  If on the way home from Martha's Vineyard you have to here and grab a pie for dessert.

Homemade everything! This place is awesome! They roast their own coffee and the aroma from the coffee roaster just adds to the atmosphere. Sandwiches, pasteries and pies are fantastic. Good luck finding parking but if you can get a spot this cozy little spot is worth checking out.

This place is awesome. There pie is delicious, and it's such a cozy place to visit in the winter. I love that they're open late at night, almost every day of the year. 
Sometimes I'll take the kids there for dessert on a random week night in the off season. There are always people there, whether locals or people traveling to the island.
They have great sandwiches and roast their own coffee.

I absolutely love this place! It's quaint, tasty n fresh plus it's right in the heart of things. Really one of a kind, I'd recommend looking at the specials and the coffee is so good. Really friendly staff😉
